                    <p>A single database is a completely isolated database optimized for workloads when performance requirements are predictable. You can shrink or expand a single database at "Basic," "Standard," and "Premium" service levels, so that you can get the performance and functions you need when your application happens to be needed. Each layer is mainly distinguished by its performance which is measured by the <a class="wa-selta" id="documentation-articles-sql-database-service-tiers-" style="color:#00a8d9;" target="_blank" href="/documentation/articles/sql-database-service-tiers/">Database Transaction Unit (DTU)</a>. See <a target="_blank" class="wa-selta" id="/documentation/articles/sql-database-service-tiers/" href="/documentation/articles/sql-database-service-tiers/" style="color:#00a8d9;">Service Layers</a> for more details.</p>
                    <h3>Basic Level</h3>
                    <p>Applications designed for light transaction workloads. The "basic" level performance goal provides a predictable hourly transaction rate.</p>
