            <div class="pricing-page-section">
                <div class="more-detail">
                    <h2>FAQ</h2>
                    <em>Expand all</em>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <i class="icon icon-plus"></i>
                            <div>
                                <a id="home_sql_database_question1">What’s the pricing for Azure SQL Database?</a>
                                <section>
                                     <p>The total price of a single database (or elastic databases) is equal to the price of DTU (or eDTU) plus the price of any pre-set extra storage. The price of DTU (or eDTU) covers storage with a certain capacity without additional costs. Once the included storage capacity is exceeded, an extra cost can be paid for additional storage capacity under the storage cap. When the needed storage capacity is less than 1 TB, it can be increased by 250 GB; when it is over 1 TB, it can be increased by 256 GB. The price of the extra storage equals the extra storage capacity multiplied by the unit price of the corresponding service layer. DTU or eDTU and any extra storage are charged by the hour.</p>
                                </section>
                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <i class="icon icon-plus"></i>
                            <div>
                                <a id="SQL_Database_question2">Example of the pricing of a single database pre-set with extra storage</a>
                                <section>
                                    <p>Suppose an S3 database is pre-set with a 1TB storage capacity. Since it has 250 GB of fixed storage capacity, its extra storage capacity is 1 TB - 250 GB = 774 GB. During the preview, the unit price of standard versions is about ￥ 0.5406/GB/month, so the price of extra storage is 774 GB * ￥ 0.5406/GB/month = RMB418.42/month. Therefore, the total price of the S3 Database is RMB969.37/month (eDTU) + RMB418.42/month of extra storage = RMB1,387.79/month.</p>
                                </section>
                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <i class="icon icon-plus"></i>
                            <div>
                                <a id="SQL_Database_question3">Example of pricing for an elastic database preset with extra storage capacity</a>
                                <section>
                                    <p>Suppose a 125 eDTU Premium pool is preset with 1 TB and that the pool has a storage capacity of 250GB, so its extra storage capacity is 1 TB - 250 GB = 774 GB. During preview, the unit price of extra storage in the Premium pool is about ￥ 1.0812/GB/month, so the price of extra storage is 774 GB * ￥ 1.0812/GB/month = RMB836.85/month. Therefore, the total price of the database equals RMB8,835.00/month (eDTU) + RMB836.85/month of extra storage = RMB9,671.85/month.</p>
                                </section>

                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <i class="icon icon-plus"></i>
                            <div>
                                <a id="SQL_Database_question4">What is the difference between Premium RS and the Premium version? </a>
                                <section>
                                     <p>Premium versions are specially designed for IO intensive generation workloads that require high availability and zero downtime. Such versions have 99.99% availability supported by service level agreements. They also have fault-tolerant capabilities and can automatically process access and write availability.</p>
                                     <p>Premium RS is designed for IO intensive workloads that can accept a limited durability guarantee and lower Service Level Agreements. The running of Premium RS reduces the number of redundant copies, which means that in the event of a service failure, capturing the backup and recovery data may require a five-minute delay.</p>
                                </section>

                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <i class="icon icon-plus"></i>
                            <div>
                                <a id="SQL_Database_question5">Does Premium RS have a Service Level Agreement? </a>
                                <section>
                                   <p>Premium RS does not provide a Service Level Agreement during public preview. When Premium RS is officially published, its service level agreement will be lower than that of the advanced version.</p>
                                </section>

                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <i class="icon icon-plus"></i>
                            <div>
                                <a id="SQL_Database_question6">Can Premium RS be upgraded to a Premium version?</a>
                                <section>
                                     <p> Yes, it can be upgraded to a Premium version at any time.</p>    
                                </section>

                            </div>
                        </li>
